      • getNodes

        public java.util.TreeSet<SWCPoint> getNodes()
                                     throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Extracts the nodes (single-point soma, axonal and dendritic arbor) of the loaded neuron.
        Returns:
        the list of nodes of the neuron as SWCPoints. Note that the first point in the set (the soma) has an SWC sample number of 0.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if retrieval of data for this neuron is not possible

      • getNodes

        public java.util.TreeSet<SWCPoint> getNodes(java.lang.String compartment)
                                     throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Script-friendly method to extract the nodes of a compartment.
        Parameters:
        compartment - 'soma', 'axon', 'dendrite', 'all' (case insensitive)
        Returns:
        the list of nodes of the neuron as SWCPoints. All nodes are retrieved if compartment was not recognized.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if compartment is not recognized or retrieval of data for this neuron is not possible

      • getSoma

        public SWCPoint getSoma()
                 throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Retrieves the soma (single-point representation) of the loaded neuron.
        Returns:
        the soma as SWCPoint. Note that point has an SWC sample number of 0.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if retrieval of data for this neuron is not possible
